1,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"**1. indexed geometry support for THREE.BufferGeometry.merge():**\nCurrently I believe adding a indexOffset parameter (which have to be set only for indexed geometries) and changing [this for loop](https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/r70\/src\/core\/BufferGeometry.js#L788-L792) to:\n\n``` javascript\nif ( key === 'index' ) {\n    for ( var i = 0, j = attributeSize * indexOffset; i < attributeArray2.length; i ++, j ++ ) {\n        attributeArray1[ j ] = attributeArray2[ i ] + offset;\n   }\n} else {\n    for ( var i = 0, j = attributeSize * offset; i < attributeArray2.length; i ++, j ++ ) {\n        attributeArray1[ j ] = attributeArray2[ i ];\n    }\n}\n```\n\nshould be enough to support indexed geometries in merge (but I'm still testing and it does not eliminate duplications as suggested in #6191).\n\n**2. Having to take care about attributes array buffer length and offsets:**\nImho I think the name merge is a little bit misleading, because it only does copy the attributes of one geometry to another geometry with a given offset, but documenting this method should lower the confusion.\nI would suggest to create either a helper function for merging geometries, which take care setting the attribute lengths and offsets to the correct value or add a second function to BufferGeometry (similar to Vector3.add vs Vector3.addVectors) which should do this.\n","created_at":"2015-03-07T19:50:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6188#issuecomment-77706652","id":77706652,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6188","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDc3NzA2NjUy","updated_at":"2016-02-18T09:40:28.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/77706652","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/chrmoritz\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/chrmoritz\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url